natural problem: If $f^{-1}(g(x))=x^3-1$ and $g$ has an inverse, find $g^{-1}(f(7))$.
natural solution: We know that $f^{-1}(u)=v$ is the same as $u=f(v)$.

Therefore, $g^{-1}(f(7))$ is the value of $x$ such that $x^3 - 1 = 7$.
